// packaging variants — same approach as before, freshly re-extracted). Unlike the previous
// version of this file, every non-trivial field is tagged with where it came from as it's
// resolved (see the assembly loop below): a direct sheet reading ('beer-list.xls'), real
// web research or established brewery knowledge (a URL, or the literal string 'knowledge'),
// or a Style Guidelines-derived fallback ('style_guideline') when neither the sheet nor
// research supplied a value. This replaces the old per-record single confidence/source
// pair with genuine per-field provenance, per the /admin/beers "Sources" column.
//
// colorFor()/flavorFor() (independent regex heuristics on the style string) have been
// deleted outright — color and flavor are now ALWAYS derived from the beer's BA style
// guideline entry (STYLE_KEY_COLOR / STYLE_KEY_FLAVOR below), never guessed from keywords
// in the beer's own name. ABV/IBU fall back to the midpoint of the BA guideline's range
// when the sheet/research didn't supply an explicit value.
//
// Image data (~58 of 450 beers) was carried over from the previous version of this file's
// hand-sourced photos, matched by normalized product name.
//
// Run:  node scripts/build-beers-enriched.mjs

